OL,6,FHe held there was no viable
OL,7,Falternative to a public inquiry
OL,8,Frequired to satisfy the state's
OL,9,Finvestigative duty under Article 2 of
OL,10,Fthe European Convention on Human
OL,11,FRights.
OL,13,FThe UK Government is challenging his
OL,14,Fruling on the grounds that it raises
OL,15,Fwider issues of constitutional
OL,16,Fsignificance beyond the case.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G7/11
